   "source": [
    "# Migraine Classification - ML Modeling\n",
    "\n",
    "## Objective\n",
    "To build a binary classification model that predicts migraine occurrence using lifestyle features including hydration, sleep, and stress levels, along with engineered lag and rolling average features.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Dataset\n",
    "Personal migraine tracking dataset with 11,079 daily records across multiple individuals.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Features Used\n",
    "- Current day: hydration_level, sleep_hours, stress_level\n",
    "- Lag features (previous day): hydration_level_lag1, sleep_hours_lag1, stress_level_lag1\n",
    "- Rolling averages (3-day): hydration_level_roll3, sleep_hours_roll3, stress_level_roll3"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "d33fcece",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(11879, 9)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('data/migraine_dataset.csv')\n",
    "print(df.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "b16eacc8",
